Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.62,0:00:05.89,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,In this world, in addition to adventurers
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.89,0:00:09.73,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,and People of the Land, there are \Nalso groups called demi-humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.53,0:00:11.74,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,For example, the goblins.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.34,0:00:16.18,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,They have limited intelligence, \Nbut are hardy and breed quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.18,0:00:18.12,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,And above all, they're cruel and wicked.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.19,0:00:24.73,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,An individual goblin is no match for an \Nadventurer of intermediate strength or higher,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.34,0:00:28.39,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,but their numbers and variety \Nare not to be underestimated.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.84,0:00:34.24,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Most of their territory is in the \Nnortheast of the island chain.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.47,0:02:10.20,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Then, what should we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.70,0:02:15.15,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I think it's a bad idea for us to attend only one.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.43,0:02:17.36,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,A banquet with Lord Darte,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.72,0:02:20.04,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,an evening party comprised \Nprimarily of young knights,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.49,0:02:24.95,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,and a dinner meeting with Count Kirino \Nof Tsukuba and the Academic's Guild...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.36,0:02:28.58,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,The Academic's Guild is a little much for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.58,0:02:29.43,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,Same here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.95,0:02:31.97,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I'll handle that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.44,0:02:35.50,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Crusty, why don't you take the \Nparty with the young knights?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.04,0:02:39.43,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure you'll enjoy the dance.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.41,0:02:43.77,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,That isn't a bad idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.42,0:02:47.43,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Then I'll take the banquet with Lord Darte.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.65,0:02:50.36,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Will you be okay, Crusty?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.36,0:02:55.19,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,You'll have to deal with flattering \Nlords and noble ladies.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.29,0:03:01.80,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,Lately, I've found a shield that's \Nso durable, it's nigh-unbreakable.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.80,0:03:03.01,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.90,0:03:05.98,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,A shield?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.93,0:03:12.88,Title,S,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1591,1)}Shield and Freedom
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.50,0:03:10.95,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Shield and Freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.09,0:03:20.38,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Lady Lenessia, it's almost bedtime.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.53,0:03:23.89,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,No, Elyssa...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.21,0:03:26.55,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not wearing the silk pajamas.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.09,0:03:28.57,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,Those are evil pajamas.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.90,0:03:31.02,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Not this again.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.20,0:03:32.91,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Then you'd prefer these?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.83,0:03:37.41,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,These are perfect!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.41,0:03:38.78,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,Flannel pajamas...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.02,0:03:41.37,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Wear the silk ones once in a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.37,0:03:42.91,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the one who gets scolded.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.91,0:03:44.78,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, eventually.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.18,0:03:51.04,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,All the gentlemen call you the \Nmelancholy twilight princess, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.86,0:03:54.55,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not melancholy. Merely gloomy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.86,0:03:57.60,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,And it isn't twilight. I'm just unmotivated.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.60,0:03:59.59,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,You won't find a gentleman who will allow you
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.59,0:04:01.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to lie around all day and do nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.50,0:04:04.55,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.46,0:04:08.71,Default - flashback,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, Lord Kiliva...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.71,0:04:11.09,Default - flashback,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,But I have another engagement.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.09,0:04:12.81,Default - flashback,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Another engagement?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.29,0:04:16.13,Default - flashback,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, with Princess Lenessia?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.27,0:04:22.01,Default - flashback,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,A pleasure to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.35,0:04:24.73,Default - flashback,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,I am the adventurer Crusty.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.73,0:04:26.54,Default - flashback,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,Pleased to make your acquaintance.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.44,0:04:30.02,Default - flashback,L,0000,0000,0000,,What did you mean by an engagement?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.54,0:04:32.86,Default - flashback,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,That was only an excuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.86,0:04:35.58,Default - flashback,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,If it caused you any problem, I apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.82,0:04:37.22,Default - flashback,L,0000,0000,0000,,N-No...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.43,0:04:42.09,Default - flashback,L,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He doesn't seem like a bad \Nperson... Merely a pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.50,0:04:45.01,Default - flashback,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,You were just thinking I'm a pain, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.58,0:04:50.25,Default - flashback,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,Not only that, but when our eyes first met,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.25,0:04:52.14,Default - flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,you thought, "What a bother."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.67,0:04:54.34,Default - flashback,L,0000,0000,0000,,H-How...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.91,0:04:58.11,Default - flashback,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,How did I know, indeed?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.62,0:05:02.54,Default - flashback,L,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He can read my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.43,0:05:05.50,Default - flashback,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,How about some tea?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.50,0:05:08.51,Default - flashback,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,The lords have been chasing \Nme around all day.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.51,0:05:10.16,Default - flashback,L,0000,0000,0000,,B-But...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.16,0:05:13.12,Default - flashback,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,I realize the prospect doesn't \Nplease you, but right now,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.12,0:05:16.50,Default - flashback,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the subject of much scrutiny in the palace.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.95,0:05:20.29,Default - flashback,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,If the two of us were to take tea together,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.68,0:05:22.56,Default - flashback,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,it would give us an excuse
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.56,0:05:25.13,Default - flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,to skip some of the ceremonies and tea parties.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.98,0:05:29.26,Default - flashback,L,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}H-He's a bad person!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.06,0:05:33.22,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Please be careful, Princess.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.04,0:05:35.52,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.52,0:05:38.32,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,He can tell what I'm thinking...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.32,0:05:39.88,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,That isn't what I mean!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.75,0:05:42.58,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,He's an adventurer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.58,0:05:45.03,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,We don't know what they're like.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.03,0:05:46.84,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.28,0:05:49.48,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,I don't like saying this,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.85,0:05:52.60,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,but you need to think more about your position
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.60,0:05:54.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as a member of Duke Cowen's family.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.11,0:05:56.46,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.01,0:06:03.20,Default - italics,L,0000,0000,0000,,A member of the duke's family, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.87,0:06:10.04,Default,Guys,0000,0000,0000,,Beautiful, as always!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.04,0:06:11.88,Default,Guys,0000,0000,0000,,How delicate!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.30,0:06:18.19,Default - italics,L,0000,0000,0000,,Half of those compliments
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.72,0:06:21.23,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,are more for my grandfather's sake than mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.30,0:06:27.70,Default - italics,L,0000,0000,0000,,With the right decoration, \Nanyone can be beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.14,0:06:30.61,Default - italics,L,0000,0000,0000,,And I can't even dress myself...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.23,0:06:36.42,Default - italics,L,0000,0000,0000,,How long will this last?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.55,0:06:53.39,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You win...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.78,0:06:57.01,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,What a splendid strike.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.01,0:06:59.12,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,I hope you can take some time to train me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.75,0:07:03.50,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,A goodwill match?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.50,0:07:05.48,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, they invited me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.48,0:07:07.96,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,That's surprising.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.96,0:07:09.12,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,What is?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.46,0:07:12.66,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you'd find such things tedious.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.66,0:07:13.68,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.68,0:07:18.29,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to know more about \Nthe People of the Land.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.98,0:07:23.09,Default - italics,L,0000,0000,0000,,Liar.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.80,0:07:26.25,Default - italics,L,0000,0000,0000,,He's looking to see if any of us are good.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.18,0:07:29.23,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Crusty?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.68,0:07:32.26,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's Princess Lenessia.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.90,0:07:34.91,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,What did you think when you fought them?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.91,0:07:36.99,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,You're an adventurer.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.99,0:07:39.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,None of them is likely to \Nbe stronger than you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.07,0:07:41.58,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,No, they were all quite talented.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.05,0:07:43.90,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,That last fight was close.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.25,0:07:46.18,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.12,0:07:47.96,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.96,0:07:51.53,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,It's difficult to fight your way \Nup and rank first here...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.61,0:07:54.89,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,Princess Lenessia?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.46,0:07:57.56,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.12,0:08:04.04,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,Princess, would you please give a reward \Nto the strongest of these brave knights?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.39,0:08:05.40,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,A reward?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.05,0:08:10.58,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,The right to accompany you \Nto this evening's party.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.82,0:08:13.55,Default,Guys,0000,0000,0000,,Th-That's great!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.55,0:08:15.30,Default,Guys,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! I'll do my best!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.23,0:08:24.37,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.76,0:08:26.02,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,That's quite a shield.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.54,0:08:32.42,Default,Guys,0000,0000,0000,,But what does Duke Cowen intend \Nto do with the adventurers?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.42,0:08:35.07,Default,Guys,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows if negotiation with \Nthem is even possible?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.53,0:08:38.95,Default,Guys,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, have we still not heard \Nwhere the Izumo Knights are?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.39,0:08:42.14,Default,Guys,0000,0000,0000,,We could just use the adventurers for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.14,0:08:44.60,Default,Guys,0000,0000,0000,,After all, they're immortal.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.81,0:08:48.84,Default,Guys,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, hello, you two...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.76,0:08:51.92,Default,Kids,0000,0000,0000,,I found you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.51,0:08:53.99,Default,Kids,0000,0000,0000,,It's that hide-and-seek genius.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.99,0:08:56.55,Default,Kids,0000,0000,0000,,Come play hide-and-seek with us!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.75,0:09:00.81,Default,Kids,0000,0000,0000,,She really is good at hide-and-seek!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.60,0:09:03.23,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not playing hide-and-seek.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.83,0:09:09.57,Default,Guys,0000,0000,0000,,Your theory denies the possibility that \Nthe People of the Land can progress!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.57,0:09:13.74,Default,Guys,0000,0000,0000,,Your refusal to admit the possibility of \Nmy theory is hindering {\i1}our{\i0} progress!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.74,0:09:16.33,Default,Guys,0000,0000,0000,,What does progress even mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.33,0:09:19.49,Default,Guys,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that where we should start?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.63,0:09:21.72,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}That is merely running away from the issue!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.98,0:09:23.09,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I guess there are heated debates in every world.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.72,0:09:23.09,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.09,0:09:24.01,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Is that your answer?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.01,0:09:26.58,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,I'm thinking of all the People \Nof the Land when I say...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.58,0:09:27.73,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Shiroe?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.73,0:09:28.75,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Minori?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.51,0:09:32.02,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,I'm heading into the dungeon now...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.57,0:09:34.77,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Can we talk for a while?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.39,0:09:37.26,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.80,0:09:39.87,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I'm right in the midst of a conference.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.22,0:09:42.40,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.40,0:09:43.38,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.38,0:09:44.57,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.57,0:09:45.74,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,I'll talk to you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.02,0:10:20.53,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You win.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.90,0:10:23.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.61,0:10:27.47,Default - italics,L,0000,0000,0000,,Well, naturally, he was going to win.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.17,0:10:44.12,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,Facing so many renowned knights is tiring.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.95,0:10:46.59,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,Was that sarcasm?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.59,0:10:48.20,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,Of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.55,0:10:53.83,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,Wake me up in a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.83,0:10:56.22,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,But... What if someone sees you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.22,0:10:57.42,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.42,0:10:59.63,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,I'm only a barbaric adventurer, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.45,0:11:04.12,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure the lords would accept it as natural.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.21,0:11:07.65,Default - italics,L,0000,0000,0000,,Somehow, it isn't fair.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.65,0:11:09.38,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,You just thought it isn't fair, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.25,0:11:12.75,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,Why not join me?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.37,0:11:15.95,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,The table is cool, and it feels nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.81,0:11:25.10,Default,Guys,0000,0000,0000,,So you're saying, it's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.10,0:11:26.16,Default,Guys,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.53,0:11:32.79,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,Adventurers are free.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.21,0:11:34.25,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,Free?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.71,0:11:36.15,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,They can eat when they like,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.15,0:11:37.82,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,sleep when they like,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.82,0:11:39.95,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,and move when they like.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.89,0:11:41.76,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.79,0:11:44.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Being free takes resolve.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.05,0:11:50.02,Default - italics,L,0000,0000,0000,,Free...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.53,0:12:09.39,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Here!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.35,0:12:25.26,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,An hour in, and look at us...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.87,0:12:28.57,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,We've done this over and over.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.98,0:12:30.37,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Why can't we win?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.44,0:12:36.01,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I'm taking damage because \Nyou guys aren't healing right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.01,0:12:37.82,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Don't talk that way!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.82,0:12:39.40,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone's doing their jobs!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.62,0:12:41.92,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Then why is this happening?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.59,0:12:45.41,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Why am I so weak?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.06,0:12:48.63,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I'm at level 24.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.63,0:12:50.87,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,The enemies range from levels 17 to 21...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.87,0:12:53.38,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,So why is it this hard?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.77,0:12:55.42,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,This doesn't make sense!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.86,0:12:56.92,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,It's because...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.24,0:13:03.03,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,It's because you aren't fighting \Nat your full potential!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.61,0:13:08.06,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Do I just need to keep training?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.76,0:13:12.43,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Will those kids be okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.09,0:13:16.19,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,It's been four days since they entered the dungeon.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.71,0:13:18.38,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.38,0:13:19.82,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,You worry too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.62,0:13:25.33,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,But what if something happens, \Nand they get sent back to Akihabara?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.33,0:13:28.32,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Then we'll use our griffins to retrieve them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.95,0:13:31.44,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,You talk like it's not your problem...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.44,0:13:35.60,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,They say lions toss their own \Ncubs off cliffs, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.60,0:13:39.06,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, but that isn't true.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.88,0:13:42.53,Default,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,You won't surpass the dungeon teams like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.93,0:13:43.96,Default,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,Fight harder!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.80,0:13:47.22,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Either way, being overprotective won't help.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.86,0:13:51.22,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,The point of this training camp is \Nto help them gain experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.31,0:13:53.77,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.77,0:13:54.85,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.85,0:13:56.98,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,I'll believe in them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.60,0:14:02.01,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I think I'll eat some crab.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.38,0:14:04.23,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.59,0:14:09.61,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,The big ones are bland.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.06,0:14:10.99,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.27,0:14:15.14,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,The new kids get training, \Nand I get to eat crab.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.14,0:14:16.87,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Two birds with one stone!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.28,0:14:24.76,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Shouryuu, what's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.43,0:14:26.68,Default,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.00,0:14:27.84,Default,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,Bubbles?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.46,0:14:29.26,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,They disappeared?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.38,0:14:33.16,Default,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.26,0:14:37.60,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,How do you like it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.60,0:14:42.40,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,This meat is known as the best in my domain.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.76,0:14:47.49,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,It's delicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.89,0:14:50.28,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,I've sent for some chefs, myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.28,0:14:52.57,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, I'll invite you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.94,0:14:54.91,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,I look forward to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.91,0:14:58.08,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,I've heard many rumors about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.52,0:15:03.98,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,This revolution has greatly \Naffected our eating habits.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.98,0:15:07.34,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone's in love with the new food.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.65,0:15:13.14,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,The people of our domain are more \Nmotivated to find good food, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.14,0:15:15.85,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Production has elevated in a number of areas.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.37,0:15:21.34,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,We've begun to be more careful in raising,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.34,0:15:25.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,harvesting, and transporting it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.05,0:15:26.11,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad to hear that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.39,0:15:29.61,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,But there's one problem...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.89,0:15:30.61,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.15,0:15:37.08,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Raising lots of food and transporting \Nit as far as possible
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.08,0:15:40.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,makes many people happy,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.46,0:15:42.90,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,and it enriches the domain.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.58,0:15:47.01,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,But transporting it over land means...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.52,0:15:49.51,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Monsters, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.68,0:15:51.10,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.31,0:15:55.39,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,And so, I have a request, Michitaka...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.67,0:15:58.55,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,You want us to defeat the goblins?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.22,0:16:03.04,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,No, there's something else we wish to request.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.99,0:16:08.23,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,The technology to transport goods by sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.05,0:16:21.43,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Princess Lenessia's sad expression...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.85,0:16:24.71,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,She must be troubled by the world's future.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.06,0:16:26.92,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,I know it's a bother,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.94,0:16:30.09,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,but you'll have to smile a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.17,0:16:34.43,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,It must be suffocating, \Nhearing the young knights' flattery.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.22,0:16:37.93,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,I think we have the same interests here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.86,0:16:40.39,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,I know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.58,0:16:45.47,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Princess Lenessia!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.47,0:16:49.43,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry to interrupt your chat.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.43,0:16:52.32,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,May we join you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.69,0:16:54.82,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,We brought cookies!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.02,0:16:59.32,Default - italics,L,0000,0000,0000,,I think they're nice girls, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.19,0:17:04.70,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,We saw you fight with your sword!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.70,0:17:06.48,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,You're strong, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.48,0:17:08.90,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,No, I still have much to learn.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.90,0:17:10.61,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be so humble.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.61,0:17:12.74,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,It took my breath away!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.74,0:17:15.82,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,I'm unworthy of praise from such beautiful ladies.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.27,0:17:17.59,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.18,0:17:20.85,Default - italics,L,0000,0000,0000,,Why is he so polite to these two,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.85,0:17:22.96,Default - italics,L,0000,0000,0000,,and so rude to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.53,0:17:25.94,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Crusty, you're special!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.94,0:17:29.23,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Of the adventurers, you're the \Nmost elegant and noble!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.71,0:17:30.75,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.75,0:17:33.41,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,We've all been talking about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.13,0:17:36.24,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,I'm very honored.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.56,0:17:40.25,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,No, that dignified elegance \Nis why Princess Lenessia
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.25,0:17:43.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,allows you to accompany her.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.99,0:17:46.26,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right, Princess?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.49,0:17:48.47,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.06,0:17:51.25,Default - italics,L,0000,0000,0000,,I w-wonder what they're talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.65,0:17:54.31,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Princess Lenessia is so beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.31,0:17:56.49,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Accompanying her must be fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.06,0:17:58.99,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,She is a kind, compassionate person.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.58,0:18:02.66,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,Her kindness allows a newcomer like myself
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.66,0:18:04.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to remain in her company.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.53,0:18:09.20,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,I am unfamiliar with courtly etiquette,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.20,0:18:14.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and she allows me to avoid looking \Nlike a country bumpkin.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.96,0:18:17.40,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,It is an honor of which I am unworthy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.22,0:18:21.16,Default - italics,L,0000,0000,0000,,He's a bad person.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.90,0:18:23.69,Default - italics,L,0000,0000,0000,,He's a really bad person!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.30,0:18:28.87,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Then, we'll introduce you to everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.87,0:18:31.50,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Once they get to know you,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.50,0:18:33.92,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,no one will mistake you for a bumpkin.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.37,0:18:37.80,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,No, I am a barbarian who knows only war.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.62,0:18:42.39,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,Until I repay the princess for the \Nkindness she's shown to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.39,0:18:44.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I cannot leave her side.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.65,0:18:49.44,Default - italics,L,0000,0000,0000,,What is his problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.33,0:18:52.18,Default,Girls,0000,0000,0000,,A knight serving his lady!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.18,0:18:53.56,Default,Girls,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1,636)}How wonderful...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.39,0:18:57.82,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,Feel free
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.19,0:19:03.28,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,to leave me behind and look at \Nthe pretty palace flowers instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.89,0:19:08.21,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,I already have my hands full with \Na single beautiful flower.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.63,0:19:12.33,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,But you know exactly how \Nto handle girls, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.64,0:19:15.09,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,It depends on the girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.16,0:19:19.88,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,In my hometown, I have a younger sister,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.88,0:19:22.44,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,so girls like you are easier for me to handle.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.36,0:19:27.35,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,A-Am I like your sister?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.77,0:19:28.68,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.41,0:19:32.47,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,Can you not see her?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.11,0:19:35.61,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,At the moment, it would be difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.74,0:19:38.54,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,You... miss her?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.72,0:19:40.88,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't say.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.14,0:19:44.23,Default - italics,L,0000,0000,0000,,He's...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.92,0:19:48.87,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,Looking at you reminds me of her.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.25,0:19:52.48,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,Putting your cheek against \Nthe table to feel its chill,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.48,0:19:55.30,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,lying around all day if you let her,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.30,0:19:57.50,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,only wearing the most comfortable clothes...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.50,0:19:58.59,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,You're just like her.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.04,0:20:00.69,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You haven't seen me do all that!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.69,0:20:02.46,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,How do you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.46,0:20:04.33,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,Because you're like her.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.80,0:20:10.02,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,In many ways, being around \Nyou eases my tired heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.98,0:20:14.64,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,Please give me the chance to repay \Nyou during the conference.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.81,0:20:17.83,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,You scratch my back, and I scratch yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.61,0:20:20.40,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,Give and take.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.16,0:20:24.04,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,Very well, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.91,0:20:40.93,Default - italics,L,0000,0000,0000,,A handshake?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.70,0:21:01.43,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,One, two, three...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.90,0:21:04.03,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,One, two, three...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.77,0:21:06.63,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Akatsuki, aren't you going to sleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.87,0:21:09.08,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,My lord...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.08,0:21:10.45,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,H-How long were you there?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.66,0:21:12.27,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.27,0:21:13.41,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I just arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.93,0:21:16.92,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Want some?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.29,0:21:21.02,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,The Academic's Guild finally released me...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.37,0:21:24.49,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,They kept pestering me to let \Nthem research adventurers.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.86,0:21:25.93,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.19,0:21:30.06,Default - italics,A,0000,0000,0000,,His hair swirls to the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.50,0:21:31.43,Default - italics,A,0000,0000,0000,,It's cute.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.70,0:21:34.02,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Well? Did you learn anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.61,0:21:39.38,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,People of the Land see us as potential enemies, \Nbut they mean us no direct harm.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.38,0:21:40.94,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Their opinion of us is about half favorable.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.31,0:21:42.65,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.25,0:21:46.07,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I believe they see us as potential \Nenemies because of our power.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.75,0:21:50.98,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Neither of us has a real idea as \Nto what the other is capable of...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.63,0:21:55.33,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,They're probably debating whether to defeat \Nus by surprise or do everything we say.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.47,0:21:58.08,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Anything else?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.69,0:22:00.16,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.16,0:22:03.34,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,they also mentioned something about still \Nnot knowing where the Izumo Knights are.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.90,0:22:05.36,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,The Izumo Knights?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.02,0:22:19.90,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,You must be Shiroe, of Log Horizon.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.90,0:22:24.23,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,I've come to speak with you tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.98,0:22:25.99,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.60,0:22:32.99,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,I am the mage Regan, of Miral Lake.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.82,0:24:09.17,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,That day, everything changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.17,0:24:11.51,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,That day, I suddenly found myself here.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.51,0:24:15.40,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,That day, the Apocalypse descended \Non tens of thousands of people.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.40,0:24:19.27,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,The Mage of Eternal Eyes, Regan, \Nspeaks regarding its secrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.70,0:24:22.84,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,Shiroe learns the rules that govern \Nthe lives of adventurers.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.23,0:24:30.99,Title,Next time,0000,0000,0000,,World Fraction
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.35,0:24:25.50,Default,Next time,0000,0000,0000,,Next time: World Fraction.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.79,0:24:28.25,Default,Next time,0000,0000,0000,,Always look thirty seconds ahead.
